# Copy to `.env` for local development. Restart Metro after changes.
# Client-safe keys only (EXPO_PUBLIC_*). RentCast + OpenAI stay in Supabase Edge secrets.

# Supabase — Dashboard → Project Settings → API (use YOUR project’s URL + anon key)
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_public_jwt_here
# Must be the same Supabase project as `supabase link` and deployed Edge functions, or auth/import/places will fail.
# After setting these, configure redirect URLs in Supabase (see docs/AUTH_DEVELOPER_CHECKLIST.md).

# RevenueCat — ONLY public *SDK* keys (never secret / sk_ keys in the app — error 7243).
# iOS: RevenueCat dashboard → API keys → Apple App Store → *public* key (prefix appl_)
# Android: public Google Play key (prefix goog_)
#
# EAS / TestFlight / App Store builds: set the same EXPO_PUBLIC_* values as EAS Secrets
# (Project → Secrets) or in the build profile `env` block so they are baked in at build time.
# Local .env is not uploaded — CI must inject them for production binaries.
# Public Apple SDK key (appl_…) — paste from RevenueCat → API keys (never use sk_ / secret keys here).
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_API_KEY_IOS=appl_YOUR_PUBLIC_APPLE_SDK_KEY
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_API_KEY_ANDROID=
# Offering identifiers (must match RevenueCat dashboard → Offerings; defaults in src/services/revenuecat/productIds.ts)
EXPO_PUBLIC_RC_SUBSCRIPTION_OFFERING_ID=propfolio_subscription
EXPO_PUBLIC_RC_CREDITS_OFFERING_ID=propfolio_credits

# Legal & support (replace example.com before production)
EXPO_PUBLIC_PRIVACY_POLICY_URL=https://example.com/propfolio/privacy
EXPO_PUBLIC_TERMS_OF_SERVICE_URL=https://example.com/propfolio/terms
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@example.com

# Optional: only if you call Google from the client elsewhere. Import uses Edge Functions + GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY secret.
# Do not commit real keys — create a key in Google Cloud Console and set locally / EAS Secrets only.
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# --- Supabase Edge Function secrets (Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets, or `supabase secrets set`) ---
# Do NOT put service-role or provider API keys in Expo .env.
#
# Hosted Supabase Edge automatically provides (you usually do NOT set these manually):
#   SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#
# Set these yourself (required for matching app behavior):
#   GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY — Places (New): autocomplete, place details, normalize-address geocoding.
#   RENTCAST_API_KEY — import-property + rent-estimate.
#   OPENAI_API_KEY — generate-property-summary only (optional if you skip AI summaries).
#   OPENAI_SUMMARY_MODEL — optional (default gpt-4o-mini in code).
#   REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_SECRET — must match RevenueCat webhook Authorization header (revenuecat-webhook).
#
# EAS / TestFlight: add EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* (and other EXPO_PUBLIC_*) as EAS Secrets so builds match local .env.
